# Research and Content Safety Use License

Version 1.0

This license applies to the videos, metadata, prompts, shards, checksums, and
dataset documentation released as the Cinematic DiT Video Dataset, unless a file
states otherwise.

## 1. Purpose

The dataset is provided for non-commercial research and evaluation related to
AI-generated video detection, media forensics, provenance analysis,
authenticity assessment, and content-safety work.

## 2. Allowed Uses

You may use the dataset to:

- train, validate, and benchmark models that detect or analyze AI-generated
  video;
- study synthetic-to-real distribution gaps, temporal artifacts, and forensic
  signals;
- reproduce non-commercial academic experiments and publish aggregate research
  findings;
- create derived statistics, labels, features, and evaluation results for the
  allowed research purposes above.

## 3. Prohibited Uses

You may not use the dataset to:

- train, fine-tune, distill, improve, benchmark, or evaluate generative video
  models, including text-to-video, image-to-video, video-to-video, animation,
  video editing, or video enhancement models;
- build, improve, or operate commercial products or services;
- create, improve, distribute, or assist deceptive, impersonating, harmful, or
  misleading synthetic media;
- present any generated video as authentic real-world footage or evidence of a
  real event;
- rehost, mirror, redistribute, sublicense, sell, rent, transfer, or publicly
  republish the videos, shards, or a substantially equivalent copy of the
  dataset;
- attempt to identify private individuals or infer sensitive personal
  attributes from generated content.

## 4. Access Control

Access is granted individually and may require a Hugging Face account,
institutional or project information, a research-purpose statement, and
acceptance of this license.

The maintainers may deny, revoke, suspend, or limit access when a request is
outside the intended scope, when misuse is suspected, when required by platform
policy, or when needed to respond to a rights-holder, service-provider, or legal
request.

## 5. Attribution

Research outputs using the dataset should cite the dataset card or associated
paper, acknowledge the dataset name, and state that the videos are synthetic.

## 6. No Warranty

The dataset is provided as is, without warranties or guarantees of quality,
fitness for a particular purpose, non-infringement, or legal suitability for
any specific use.

## 7. Third-Party Rights and Terms

This license grants only rights that the maintainers can grant. It does not
override third-party intellectual-property rights, personality rights, privacy
rights, service-provider terms, platform terms, or applicable law. Users are
responsible for ensuring that their use is lawful and permitted.

## 8. Termination

Your rights under this license terminate automatically if you violate its
terms. Upon termination, you must stop using the dataset and delete any local
copies of the videos and shards, except for derived aggregate results that do
not contain or reconstruct the original videos.
